const faqItems = [{"question": "How do I get my Birmingham dental practice recommended by ChatGPT?", "answer": "ChatGPT recommends practices it can verify. For a Birmingham dentist, that means a complete GDC register entry that matches your website, a Google Business Profile with current photos and hours, treatment specific pages on your own site (Invisalign, implants, hygienist, emergency), and reviews on Google plus a healthcare specific platform such as Doctify. Do those four and you usually start appearing in AI answers within weeks."}, {"question": "Why do AI tools sometimes show the wrong information about my Birmingham dental practice?", "answer": "AI tools build a picture of your practice from every public source they can find. If your name, address or services are inconsistent across your website, Google Business Profile, NHS Choices, the GDC register and review platforms, the AI picks the version that looks most cited, even if that version is wrong. The fix is to align every platform to the same details."}, {"question": "Are private dentists in Birmingham more visible in AI search than NHS practices?", "answer": "Not by default. AI tools weight clarity and trust signals, not private versus NHS status. A private practice with a clean GDC entry, treatment pages and reviews will outperform a poorly documented private practice. The same applies to NHS practices. The differentiator is how clearly the practice describes what it does and how consistent that story is across the web."}, {"question": "What treatments should a Birmingham dentist write content about for AI visibility?", "answer": "Focus on the treatments people actually search for in conversational queries: clear aligners and Invisalign, dental implants, composite bonding, cosmetic dentistry, emergency appointments and hygienist services. Each treatment deserves its own page that answers the questions a Birmingham patient would type into ChatGPT, with prices ranges where you can give them, treatment time and what the consultation involves."}, {"question": "How does a Birmingham dentist appear in Google AI Overviews?", "answer": "Google AI Overviews almost always pull from pages that already rank in the top 10 of organic results for the query. So the route is two part: rank in classic SEO first, then make sure your content includes short factual answer blocks that Google can pull cleanly. Schema markup (LocalBusiness, MedicalBusiness, FAQPage) plus Google Business Profile completeness are the technical baseline."}, {"question": "What does an AI search audit show for a Birmingham dental practice?", "answer": "You see exactly which AI tools currently mention your practice when a Birmingham resident asks for a recommendation, which competitors get named instead, and the specific signals (entity clarity, ecosystem validation, schema, reviews, content gaps) that explain the difference. The audit is written and delivered in five working days."}];
